The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assignment response[idx_response] = '\0'; writes a NUL terminator into the allocated buffer but that byte is never read: the code sends response using send_all(..., idx_response) (which does not include the terminator) and then frees the buffer. The assignment is executed but has no effect on observable program behaviour in this context, so it constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
